# Phase Exit Walkthrough — Earn The "Passed" Stamp

The `phase-walkthrough-flag.sh` hook detects when a `*-VERIFICATION.md` is updated to contain `status: passed`. The aggregator gate blocks your final response until the `phase-walkthrough-clear.sh` hook sees a `browser-harness` invocation that captured a screenshot.

## Required walkthrough

For any phase that touched frontend surfaces:

```bash
browser-harness <<'PY'
import base64, time

new_tab("http://localhost:5173/<most-changed-route>")
wait_for_load()
time.sleep(2)

# Perform the user task FROM A FRESH STATE — no prior knowledge of where the
# button is. If the button is not findable in <=2 clicks from the route above,
# the phase fails on discoverability.
js("...")  # interact

time.sleep(2)
text = js("document.body.innerText")
assert "<observable outcome>" in text, f"User journey did not produce visible outcome: {text[:300]}"

result = cdp("Page.captureScreenshot", format="png")
with open("/tmp/phase-<N>-walkthrough.png", "wb") as f:
    f.write(base64.b64decode(result["data"]))
print("PASS — walkthrough screenshot saved")
PY
```

Embed the screenshot path in `VERIFICATION.md` as evidence.

## What this catches

- Features that ship without a UI trigger (phases 6/7 catalog similarity).
- Features that ship with a UI trigger but no result surface.
- UI proportion / regression bugs that don't manifest in jest/vitest tests.
- "Passed" verifications that read code and tests but never use the feature.

## Phases that don't touch frontend

If a phase is purely backend (no `apps/visualizer/frontend/**` edits), it is exempt. Add `walkthrough_exempt: true` under the front-matter of `*-VERIFICATION.md` and the gate passes after editing.

## Why this exists

`07.1-VERIFICATION.md` was marked `status: passed` with `gaps: []` while phase 7.1 still had: (a) no UI trigger for `batch_stack_detect` and `batch_catalog_similarity`, (b) duplicated stack badge derivation across two grids, (c) `Show stack` button breaking grid proportions. A fresh-page walkthrough would have surfaced all three immediately.
